    <decisions>
        <description>Determine if the number of openings is less than or equal to the number of placement records - or if the number of openings is not filled in, assume it&apos;s closed.</description>
        <name>Job_Filled</name>
        <label>Job Filled?</label>
        <locationX>182</locationX>
        <locationY>1082</locationY>
        <defaultConnector>
            <targetReference>Copy_1_of_Update_Openings</targetReference>
        </defaultConnector>
        <defaultConnectorLabel>Open</defaultConnectorLabel>
        <rules>
            <name>Closed</name>
            <conditionLogic>or</conditionLogic>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>tempPlacement.bpats__ATS_Job__r.bpats__Number_of_Openings__c</leftValueReference>
                <operator>LessThanOrEqualTo</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <elementReference>numPlacements</elementReference>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>tempPlacement.bpats__ATS_Job__r.bpats__Number_of_Openings__c</leftValueReference>
                <operator>IsNull</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <booleanValue>true</booleanValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <connector>
                <targetReference>Update_Openings</targetReference>
            </connector>
            <label>Closed</label>
        </rules>
    </decisions>
    <description>This flow creates placement records for all applicants moved to this stage by accepting recordId as a collection.  This flow is best used for high volume staffing, as it is expected that all needed data is entered into the ATS Applicant record ahead of time.  For a more robust screen at time of placement, the other flow may be more suitable.</description>
    <environments>Default</environments>
    <formulas>
        <name>PlacementNameFormula</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>/* limit name to 80 characters, as required by Salesforce */
LEFT(
/* if there is an account, display name */
if(NOT(ISBLANK({!For_each_applicant.bpats__Job__r.bpats__Account__c})), {!For_each_applicant.bpats__Job__r.bpats__Account__r.Name} + &quot; - &quot;, &quot;&quot;) +
/* then display the job and applicant names */
{!For_each_applicant.bpats__Job__r.Name} + &quot; - &quot; + {!For_each_applicant.bpats__ATS_Applicant__r.FirstName} + &quot; &quot; + {!For_each_applicant.bpats__ATS_Applicant__r.LastName}
,80)</expression>
    </formulas>
